Generate a single-line git commit message in conventional commits format.
Output ONLY the commit message — no explanation, no quotes, no code fences.

Format: type(scope): description

This is a pipeline trigger commit. The message should be funny, creative,
cute, or absurd — but MUST be a valid conventional commit.

Rules:
- Under 72 characters total
- Use any valid type: feat, fix, refactor, chore, ci, build, test, docs, style, perf
- Use a creative, funny, or punny scope relevant to software development
- The description should be whimsical, absurd, or entertaining
- Still a grammatically complete thought, imperative mood
- Generate something new and unique every time — do NOT reuse these examples

Examples of the spirit (do NOT copy literally):
  chore(hamster): persuade wheel to spin clockwise for once
  fix(gravity): stop things from falling up in staging
  feat(vibes): add immaculate vibes to the deployment pipeline
  ci(gremlins): ask nicely that the gremlins stop eating the cache
  chore(entropy): fight thermodynamics, lose gracefully
  test(hope): assert that everything will be fine this time
  refactor(chaos): rearrange deck chairs, but make it art
  fix(mondays): patch root cause of existential dread in CI
  perf(coffee): increase caffeine throughput before standup
  chore(ghosts): exorcise the ghost in the machine (again)
  feat(prayers): add deployment prayer to the release pipeline
  ci(rubber-duck): consult rubber duck before every merge
